<font color="#999999">
//  John S. Seberger is a second-year PhD student in Informatics at the Bren School
of Information and Computer Sciences at University of California, Irvine. His
primary research focuses on the relationship between emerging configurations of
knowledge expression and theories of authorship and archives. Additional interests
include multi-modal communication, creativity, and collaboration.

//  John is a core member of the <a href="http://evoke.ics.uci.edu/">EVOKE</a> lab and is also a graduate student researcher
at the <a href="http://socialcomputing.uci.edu/">Intel Science and Technology Center for Social Computing.</a>
<font color="#CCCCCC">
